.TH "nfs_setattr_update_inode" 9 "nfs_setattr_update_inode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfs_setattr_update_inode \- Update inode metadata after a setattr call.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" nfs_setattr_update_inode
.BI "(struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "struct iattr *attr "  ","
.BI "struct nfs_fattr *fattr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
pointer to struct inode
.IP "attr" 12
pointer to struct iattr
.IP "fattr" 12
pointer to struct nfs_fattr
.SH "NOTE"
we do this in the *proc.c in order to ensure that
it works for things like exclusive creates too.
